Material Information Summary

Exploration Results Announcement

  • Key Drill Intercept:
  • 25PRCDD206: 15.5m @ 12 g/t Au (incl. 8.5m @ 20.8 g/t Au) within 54.2m @ 3.7 g/t Au at ~380m vertical depth.
  • Conductor Plates (DHEM):
  • 15 plates identified, validating conductivity-gold correlation.
  • C9 (100m x 80m) & C13 (80m x 80m) extend mineralization ~50m west, suggesting resource upside.
  • Untested northern (C10, C11) and southern (C14, C15) plates indicate expansion potential beyond current MRE.
  • Mineralized Corridor:
  • Plates C1, C8, C9, C12, C13 define a ~240m strike-length corridor, open at depth and along strike.
  • Metallurgy:
  • Gold recoveries 90.9–99.7% (gravity + CIL); low reagent consumption.
  • Resource Context:
  • Current MRE: 250koz Au @ 3.1 g/t (open in multiple directions).

No material capital markets actions (e.g., raising, trading halt) identified.

Material Information Summary:

  • Scheme Withdrawal
  • Platinum Capital withdraws proposed scheme of arrangement with Platinum International Fund Complex ETF (PIXX) due to insufficient shareholder support (requires 75% approval).

  • L1 Capital proposes replacing Platinum’s management with its own Global Long Short strategy, subject to shareholder approval.

  • General Meeting: 12 August 2025 (buy-back vote).
  • EGM for Board Changes: Date to be announced.

  3. Phase 2 Statement of Work (SOW) to commence Q1 FY26.

  4. Cell & Gene Therapy

  5. Validation data shows 96% viability vs. industry standard (70%).

  6. Revenue-generating collaborations under discussion.

  7. Aquaculture/Bovine

  8. Paid pilots with domestic providers; fertilization outcomes competitive vs. fresh samples.

  9. Global market expansion in animal reproduction pursued (e.g., Select Sires collaboration).

  10. Technology Development (VCU2 Hardware & LifeChain Software)

  11. Unregulated market launch targeted H1 FY26; regulated (medical device) launch H2 FY26 (USA).
  12. $4.8m grant secured to support commercialization.

FY26 Outlook

  • Focus on revenue generation:

  • Advance blood platelets Phase 2 and human health collaborations.
  • Execute product launches (unregulated/regulated markets).

Key Non-Material Omissions

  • Leadership bios, disclaimer boilerplate, and general market commentary excluded.
